,Recommended,327390,22228813,"Posted: 3 April, 2016",all,The Bear of Bad News,"10/10. One of Sid's early classics. I really miss the maximum replayability of 90's video games. For its time, I can't think of a single thing that would make this game better, even after 20 years of playing it (and STILL not being brave enough to go past the bottom difficulty level! XD)If you want to talk about games using random generators for each session of playing, that's this. EVERYTHING is perfectly randomized EVERY. SINGLE. TIME. I love it. Maximizes the playability. :DBut no one knows the feeling of your heart sinking when you find a floor safe, photograph it, and it has only grenades, a floor plan, or (worst of all) NOTHING!!! Come on, man! I wanna turn this dude into a double agent! :'(So yeah. 90s ingenuity and maximum replayability are huge factors in this game. Shoot, I'm still playing it 20 years later!How many modern games do you think will be playable again and again in 20 years? What titles?"
